obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (70499)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title Title.
  content `This Act may be called the North-Western Provinces and Oudh Act, 1890.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70499&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (70500)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Commencement of Part I.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70500&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `This Part shall come into force on such day^1`
  line `as the said LieutenantGovernor may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (70501)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `3 and 4 Repealed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70501&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Amendment of Act 19 of 1873. Rep. by the United Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1901`
  line `(U.P. Act 3 of 1901).`
  line
  line `And whereas it has been determined to annex the Jhansi Division, comprising the districts of Jhansi,`
  line `Jalaun and Lalatpur, to the Allahabad Division;`
  line `And whereas the said Jhansi Division is a Schedule District under the Scheduled Districts`
  line `Act, 1874; (14 of 1874);^2`
  line
  line `And whereas it is expedient that the law in force in the same division should, on such annexation, be`
  line `the same as the law in force in the temporarily-settled districts comprised in the Allahabad Division, and`
  line `that the said division should cease to be a Schedule District;`
  line
  line `It is hereby enacted as follows:—`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The 1st April, 1891, see North-Western Provinces and Oudh Gazette,1891, Pt. I, p. 130.`
  line
  line `2. Since rep. by the A.O. 1937`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (70502)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 4
  title `Laws in force in certain districts of the Allahabad Division to apply to Jhansi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70502&sectionno=5&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) All`
  line `enactments which shall on the day^1 when this Part comes into force be in force in the said temporarilysettled districts and not in the said Jhansi Division shall be deemed to come into force in that Division`
  line `on and from the said day^1.`
  line `(2) Except the Jhansi Encumbered Estates Act, 1882, (16 of 1882)^2`
  line `and the Jhansi and Morar`
  line `Act, 1886,(17 of 1886)^3`
  line `all enactments which shall on the said day^1`
  line `be in force in the said division and`
  line `not in the said temporarily settled districts, including the Jhansi Courts Act, 1867 (18 of 1867), and`
  line `Act No. 27 of 1867, shall be deemed to be repealed on and from the said day^1`
  line `in the said division.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. That is, the 1st April, 1891.`
  line
  line `2. Since rep. by the Bundelkhand`
  line `Encumbered Estates Act, 1903 (U.P. 1 of 1903).`
  line
  line `3. Rep. by Act 42 of 1953.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (70503)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 5
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70503&sectionno=6&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Rep. by the Bundelkhand Encumbered Estates Act, 1903 (U.P.`
  line `Act 1 of 1903).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (70564)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 6
  title `Discharge of functions assigned to Deputy Commissioner and Commissioner by Act 17 of 1866.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70564&sectionno=7&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The functions assigned to the Deputy Commissioner and the Commissioner by the Jhansi and`
  line `Morar Act, 1886^1`
  line `(17 of 1886), shall be discharged by the District Judge and the High Court,`
  line `respectively, and references to Courts in the Jhansi district subordinate to the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to apply to the Civil Courts established in that district under the Bengal, ^2North-Western`
  line `Provinces and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 (12 of 1887).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Rep. by Act 42 of 1953.`
  line
  line `2. “Agra” has been subs. for “North-Western Provinces” by Act 16 of 1911.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (70505)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 7
  title `Jhansi Division to cease to be a Scheduled District.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70505&sectionno=8&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the said day^1`
  line `the said`
  line `division shall cease to be a Schedule District ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. That is, the 1st April, 1891.`
  line
  line `2. The second clause of sub-section (1), and sub-section (2) were rep. by Act 1 of 1938, s. 2 and Sch`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (70506)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 8
  title `Application of Act 12 of 1887 to Jhansi, and disposal of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70506&sectionno=9&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line ^1***
  line `(2) All cases or proceedings pending in any Civil Court in the said division on the said day^2`
  line shall
  line `be disposed of as follows:—`
  line
  line `(a) if pending in theCourt of a Tahsildar or of an Assistant Commissioner of the second class—`
  line `by the Munsif;`
  line
  line `(b) if pending in the Court of an Assistant Commissioner of the first class—by the Subordinate`
  line Judge;
  line
  line `(c) if pending in the Court of a Deputy Commissioner—by the District Judge;`
  line
  line `(d) if pending in the Court of the Commissioner—by the District Judge, unless the case`
  line `pending is an appeal from a decree or order of the Deputy Commissioner, in which case the appeal`
  line `shall be disposed of by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sections 20 to 22, both inclusive, of the Bengal, ^3North-Western Provinces`
  line `and Assam Civil Courts Act, 1887 (12 of 1887), all decrees and orders passed by Civil Courts in the`
  line `said division and not appealed against before the said day3`
  line `shall be deemed—`
  line
  line `(a) if passed by the Court of a Tahsildar or an Assistant Commissioner of the second class—to`
  line `have been passed by a Munsif;`
  line
  line `(b) if passed by the Court of an Assistant Commissioner of the first class—to have been passed`
  line `by a Subordinate Judge;`
  line
  line `(c) if passed by the Court of a Deputy Commissioner or the Commissioner—to have been`
  line `passed by a District Judge.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any Civil Court ceases by reason of the passing of this Act to have jurisdiction with`
  line `respect to any case, any proceeding in relation to that case which, if that Court had not ceased to have`
  line `jurisdiction, might have been had therein, may be had in the Court to which the business of the former`
  line `Court is transferred by sub-section (2); but this sub-section shall not apply to cases for which provision`
  line `is made in section 623 or section 649 of the Code of Civil Procedure1`
  line `(14 of 1882).`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of appeals from the decrees and orders mentioned in sub-section (3) the period of`
  line `limitation shall be calculated in accordance with the provisions of section 15 of the Jhansi Courts`
  line `Act, 18672`
  line `(18 of 1867), as though this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Sub-section (1) rep., by Act 1 of 1938.`
  line
  line `2. That is, the 1st April, 1891.`
  line
  line `3. “Agra” has been subs. for “North-Western Provinces” by Act 16 of 1911.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (70507)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 9
  title `Commencement of Part II.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70507&sectionno=10&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `This Part shall come into force on such day^1`
  line `as the Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Oudh may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st January, 1891, see the North-Western Provinces and Oudh`
  line `Gazette, 1890, Pt. I, p.661.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (70565)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 10
  title `Board of Revenue of the North-Western Provinces to be the Board of Revenue of, and Chief Revenue-authority in, Oudh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70565&sectionno=11&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the day on which this Part comes into force`
  line `the Board of Revenue constituted under the North-Western Provinces Land-revenue Act, 1873^1`
  line `(19 of 1873), shall be deemed to be also the Board of Revenue for the territories administered by the Chief Commissioner of Oudh, and shall be known and designated as the Board of Revenue of the NorthWestern Provinces and Oudh^2.`
  line
  line `(2) All references made in any enactment as amended by this Part to the Board of Revenue shall be`
  line `deemed, so far as they relate to Oudh, to refer to the said Board.`
  line
  line `(3) In any enactment for the time being in force in the territories administered by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner of Oudh, in which the expression “Chief Revenue-authority” or “Chief Controlling`
  line `Revenue-authority” is used, the expression shall, subject to the provisions of any enactment passed`
  line `after the said day^3`
  line `, be construed, so far as the said territories are concerned, as referring to the Board`
  line `of Revenue of the North-Western Provinces and Oudh^2`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Since rep. by the U.P. Land-revenue Act,1901 (U.P. 3 of 1901), s. 2, but not so as to affect anything done under Act 19 of`
  line `1873, see s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Now the Board of Revenue of the U.P.`
  line
  line `3. 1st January, 1891, see the North-Western Provinces and Oudh Gazette, 1890, Pt. I, p.661.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
