  sectionId (70560)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 62
  title `Place where the Board may sit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135&sectionId=70560&sectionno=63&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00114_189020_1666335792135
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything ^1`
  line `*** in section 128 of the`
  line `Oudh Rent Act, 1886 (22 of 1886), the Board of Revenue of the North-Western Provinces and Oudh`
  line `shall, for the disposal of cases under those Acts, sit in such place or places in the North-Western`
  line `Provinces or Oudh as ^2[`
  line `the State Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette,6`
  line `appoint in`
  line `respect to cases under either of those Acts.`
  line
  line `(2) For the disposal of cases other than those referred to in sub-section (1) the said Board may,`
  line `subject to the orders of ^2[the State Government], sit in any place in the North-Western Provinces or`
  line `Oudh that the Board thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 63, so far as it relates to Act 12 of 1881, that is the words “in s. 152 of the North-Western Provinces Rent`
  line `Act, 1881, or” were rep. by the Agra Tenancy Act, 1901 (U.P. 2 of 1901).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by the A.O. 1937 for “the said Lieutenant-Governor and Chief Commissioner”`
